lead_paragraph: The Constitutionel says: "A communication is spoken of, which the French Government proposes to make to the Government of the United States, on the subject of the affairs of Cuba. The English Government, to whom ours has communicated its resolution, has replied that its intention is to make an analogous communication to the Cabinet at Washington."
